== The Abe Clan and Tsuchimikado Family ==
{{main|Abe clan (Onmyōdō)|Tsuchimikado family (Abe clan)}}
The Abe clan, beginning with the renowned {{ill|Abe no Seimei|ja|安倍晴明|qq=draft}}, was the hereditary custodian of {{ill|Tenmondō|ja|天文道|1=Tenmondō (astrology)|lt=Tenmondō|qq= (astrology)|qq=draft}}. The main line began using the name "Tsuchimikado" during the Muromachi period, with {{ill|Abe no Ariyo|ja|安倍有世|qq=draft}} often recognized as the first Tsuchimikado patriarch. However, some sources attribute this naming convention to {{ill|Tsuchimikado Arinobu|ja|土御門有宣|qq=draft}}.

The last male head of the Tsuchimikado family, {{ill|Tsuchimikado Noritada|ja|土御門範忠|qq=draft}} (1920–1994), was succeeded by his daughter Yoshiko Tsuchimikado (born 1959). This makes her the 34th generation descendant of Abe no Seimei and the 18th generation descendant of Tsuchimikado Arinobu.{{Efn2|For details on the lineage, see {{ill|Tsuchimikado Arinobu#Descendants|ja|土御門有脩#末裔}}.}}{{Efn2|No verified male-line descendants of Abe no Seimei are publicly documented.}}

